あるがまま = あるがまま = arugamama = as things are, accepting reality as it is.
人生をあるがままに生きる。 = じんせいを あるがままに いきる = jinsei o arugamama ni ikiru = Live life as it is.
一期一会 = いちごいちえ = ichigo ichie = once-in-a-lifetime encounter - Cherishing each moment as unique.
一期一会の出会いを大切に。 = いちごいちえの であいを たいせつに = ichigo ichie no deai o taisetsu ni = Treasure every once-in-a-lifetime meeting.
はんこ = はんこ = hanko = hanko stamp, personal seal - Japanese name stamp used instead of signature.
書類にはんこを押した。 = しょるいにはんこを おした = shorui ni hanko o oshita = I stamped the document with my hanko.
会釈 = えしゃく = eshaku = light greeting bow (15°) - Casual bow for acquaintances.
軽く会釈して挨拶した。 = かるく えしゃくして あいさつした = karuku eshaku shite aisatsu shita = I greeted him with a light bow.
敬礼 = けいれい = keirei = respectful bow (30-40°) - Business or formal bow toward superiors.
上司に敬礼した。 = じょうしに けいれいした = jōshi ni keirei shita = I bowed respectfully to my boss.
最敬礼 = さいけいれい = saikeirei = deepest reverent bow (45°+) - For high respect or formal occasions.
社長に最敬礼をした。 = しゃちょうに さいけいれいをした = shachō ni saikeirei o shita = I gave the deepest bow to the president.
土下座 = どげざ = dogeza = dogeza (kneeling bow with forehead to ground) - Extreme bow for deep apology.
土下座して謝った。 = どげざして あやまった = dogeza shite ayamatta = I apologized on my knees with my forehead to the ground.
お宝 = おたから = otakara = treasure, valuable possession, cherished item - Often used casually for precious things.
このゲームでお宝を見つけた！ = このゲームで おたからを みつけた！ = kono gēmu de otakara o mitsuketa! = I found treasure in this game!
財宝 = ざいほう = zaihō = treasure, wealth - Valuable objects or riches.
海賊が財宝を隠した。 = かいぞくが ざいほうを かくした = kaizoku ga zaihō o kakushita = The pirates hid the treasure.
まさか = まさか = masaka = no way, impossible, you can't be serious - Expresses disbelief.
まさか本当なのか？ = まさか ほんとうなのか？ = masaka hontō na no ka? = No way, is that true?
歳月 = さいげつ = saigetsu = years, passage of time - The flow of years/time.
歳月が人を変える。 = さいげつが ひとを かえる = saigetsu ga hito o kaeru = Time changes people.
ずいぶん = ずいぶん = zuibun = very, quite, considerably, surprisingly - Indicates degree or surprise.
ずいぶん寒くなったね。 = ずいぶん さむくなったね = zuibun samuku natta ne = It’s gotten quite cold, hasn’t it?
とりあえず = とりあえず = toriaezu = for now, tentatively, first of all - Temporary measure.
とりあえずこれでいいよ。 = とりあえず これで いいよ = toriaezu kore de ii yo = This will do for now.
つまり = つまり = tsumari = in other words, basically - Used to summarize or clarify.
つまり君の言うことは間違ってるよ。 = つまり きみの いうことは まちがってるよ = tsumari kimi no iu koto wa machigatteru yo = In other words, you’re wrong.
つもり = つもり = tsumori = intention, plan, purpose - What one intends to do.
留学するつもりだ。 = りゅうがくする つもりだ = ryūgaku suru tsumori da = I intend to study abroad.
素晴らしい = すばらしい = subarashī = wonderful, amazing, excellent, superb - Strong admiration.
この景色は素晴らしい！ = このけしきは すばらしい！ = kono keshiki wa subarashī! = This view is amazing!
約束 = やくそく = yakusoku = promise, appointment, agreement - Casual promise or formal arrangement.
約束を守るのが大事だ。 = やくそくを まもるのが だいじだ = yakusoku o mamoru no ga daiji da = Keeping promises is important.
済まない = すまない = sumanai = I'm sorry (informal), excuse me - Casual apology with regret.
本当に済まない。 = ほんとうに すまない = hontō ni sumanai = I’m really sorry.
安心する = あんしんする = anshin suru = to feel relieved, to be at ease.
安心して大丈夫だよ。 = あんしんして だいじょうぶだよ = anshin shite daijōbu da yo = Don’t worry, it’s okay.
さすが = さすが = sasuga = as expected, impressive as usual - Compliment for living up to reputation.
さすがプロだね。 = さすが プロだね = sasuga puro da ne = As expected from a pro.
無理 = むり = muri = impossible, unreasonable, excessive - Beyond one’s power or “no way”.
それは無理だと思う。 = それは むりだ とおもう = sore wa muri da to omou = I think that’s impossible.
気づかない = きづかない = kizukanai = to not notice, to be unaware.
彼は自分の間違いに気づかない。 = かれは じぶんの まちがいに きづかない = kare wa jibun no machigai ni kizukanai = He doesn’t notice his own mistake.
暗黒 = あんこく = ankoku = darkness (evil/sinister), dark age - Negative or evil darkness.
暗黒の時代が続いた。 = あんこくの じだいが つづいた = ankoku no jidai ga tsuzuita = A dark age continued.
生き延びる = いきのびる = ikinobiru = to survive, to live on - Continue existing through danger.
厳しい状況でも生き延びた。 = きびしい じょうきょうでも いきのびた = kibishii jōkyō demo ikinobita = He survived even in harsh conditions.
真実 = しんじつ = shinjitsu = truth, sincerity - Facing or speaking the truth.
真実を話してくれ。 = しんじつを はなしてくれ = shinjitsu o hanashite kure = Tell me the truth.
実際 = じっさい = jissai = reality, actuality, in practice - Real-life situation.
実際にはそんなに簡単じゃない。 = じっさいには そんなに かんたんじゃない = jissai ni wa sonna ni kantan ja nai = In reality, it’s not that simple.
無効化 = むこうか = mukōka = disabling, invalidation, override - Making something no longer valid.
システムを無効化する。 = システムを むこうかする = shisutemu o mukōka suru = Disable the system.
はずだ = はずだ = hazu da = is supposed to be, expected to be - Strong logical expectation.
彼はもう着いているはずだ。 = かれは もう ついているはずだ = kare wa mō tsuite iru hazu da = He should have arrived by now.
ふざける = ふざける = fuzakeru = to play around, to kid, to mess around - "fuzakeruna" = stop kidding.
ふざけるなよ！ = ふざけるなよ！ = fuzakeruna yo! = Stop kidding around!
確かに = たしかに = tashikani = definitely, surely, certainly - Strong agreement or realization.
確かにその通りだ。 = たしかに そのとおりだ = tashikani sono tōri da = That’s definitely true.
現在 = げんざい = genzai = now, current, present time - The present moment.
現在は何時ですか？ = げんざいは なんじですか？ = genzai wa nanji desu ka? = What time is it now?
手伝う = てつだう = tetsudau = to help, to lend a hand with work - Collaborative help.
荷物を持つ手伝いをします。 = にもつを もつ てつだいを します = nimotsu o motsu tetsudai o shimasu = I’ll help carry the luggage.
助ける = たすける = tasukeru = to help, to rescue, to save - Help in crisis or danger.
危ない！助けて！ = あぶない！ たすけて！ = abunai! tasukete! = Watch out! Help!
瓦解 = がかい = gakai = collapse, crumbling (of a system) - System or group falling apart.
組織が瓦解した。 = そしきが がかいした = soshiki ga gakai shita = The organization collapsed.
売国奴 = ばいこくど = baikokudo = traitor to one’s country - Strong term for national betrayer.
彼を売国奴と呼んだ。 = かれを ばいこくどと よんだ = kare o baikokudo to yonda = They called him a traitor to the country.
忘却 = ぼうきゃく = bōkyaku = forgetfulness, oblivion - Deliberately putting something out of mind.
過去を忘却する。 = かこを ぼうきゃくする = kako o bōkyaku suru = Forget the past completely.
監獄 = かんごく = kangoku = prison, jail - Formal term for prison.
監獄に入れられた。 = かんごくに いれられた = kangoku ni irerareta = He was put in prison.
裸の王様 = はだかのおうさま = hadaka no ōsama = the naked king / Emperor’s New Clothes - Situation where people pretend to see what isn’t there.
それは裸の王様だ。 = それは はだかのおうさまだ = sore wa hadaka no ōsama da = That’s just the Emperor’s New Clothes situation.
狼狽売り = ろうばいうり = rōbaiuri = panic selling - Selling in panic (stock market).
株価下落で狼狽売りが起きた。 = かぶかげらくで ろうばいうりが おきた = kabuka geraku de rōbaiuri ga okita = Panic selling occurred due to the stock drop.
組み立て = くみたて = kumitate = assembly, putting together - Building or assembling parts.
家具の組み立てを手伝う。 = かぐの くみたてを てつだう = kagu no kumitate o tetsudau = Help with assembling the furniture.
効率 = こうりつ = kōritsu = efficiency - Doing things with minimal waste.
効率を上げる方法を考えよう。 = こうりつを あげる ほうほうを かんがえよう = kōritsu o ageru hōhō o kangaeyō = Let’s think of ways to improve efficiency.
起死回生 = きしかいせい = kishikaisei = dramatic comeback, resuscitation - Revival from a desperate situation.
起死回生の一手が必要だ。 = きしかいせいの いってが ひつようだ = kishikaisei no itte ga hitsuyō da = We need a dramatic comeback move.
漁夫の利 = ぎょふのり = gyofu no ri = fisherman’s profit - Gaining benefit while others fight.
漁夫の利を得た。 = ぎょふのりを えた = gyofu no ri o eta = He gained the fisherman’s profit.
二兎を追う者は一兎をも得ず = にうをおうものはいつをもえず = nito o ou mono wa itto mo ezu = he who chases two rabbits catches neither.
二兎を追う者は一兎をも得ずという proverb だ。 = にうをおうものはいつをもえずという proverb だ = nito o ou mono wa itto mo ezu to iu proverb da = It’s the proverb “he who chases two rabbits catches neither.”
千里眼 = せんりがん = senrigan = far-sighted vision, clairvoyance - Ability to see far ahead.
彼は千里眼を持っているようだ。 = かれは せんりがんを もっているようだ = kare wa senrigan o motte iru yō da = He seems to have far-sighted vision.
油断大敵 = ゆだんたいてき = yudan taiteki = negligence is a great enemy.
油断大敵だから気をつけろ。 = ゆだんたいてきだから きをつけろ = yudan taiteki dakara ki o tsukero = Negligence is a great enemy, so be careful.
一石二鳥 = いっせきにちょう = isseki nichō = one stone two birds - Achieving two things with one action.
この方法は一石二鳥だ。 = このほうほうは いっせきにちょうだ = kono hōhō wa isseki nichō da = This method kills two birds with one stone.
見つける = みつける = mitsukeru = to find, to discover - Action of locating something hidden.
みんなを見つけます。 = みんなを みつけます = minna o mitsukemasu = I will find everyone.
豪華 = ごうか = gōka = luxurious, splendid, extravagant, gorgeous - Visually impressive and opulent.
豪華なパーティーだった。 = ごうかな パーティーだった = gōka na pātī datta = It was a luxurious party.
凝っている = こっている = koutte iru = elaborate, intricate, sophisticated - High-effort refined design.
この時計のデザインは凝っている。 = このとけいの デザインは こっている = kono tokei no dezain wa koutte iru = This watch has a very elaborate design.
救急車 = きゅうきゅうしゃ = kyūkyūsha = ambulance - Emergency medical transport vehicle.
救急車を呼んで！ = きゅうきゅうしゃを よんで！ = kyūkyūsha o yonde! = Call an ambulance!
救急隊 = きゅうきゅうたい = kyūkyūtai = ambulance crew, emergency medical team - The personnel on the ambulance.
救急隊が到着した。 = きゅうきゅうたいが とうちゃくした = kyūkyūtai ga tōchaku shita = The ambulance crew has arrived.
救急医療 = きゅうきゅういりょう = kyūkyū iryō = emergency medicine, emergency care - Urgent medical services.
この病院は救急医療が充実している。 = このびょういんは きゅうきゅういりょうが じゅうじつしている = kono byōin wa kyūkyū iryō ga jūjitsu shite iru = This hospital has excellent emergency medical care.
一生懸命 = いっしょうけんめい = isshōkenmei = with all one’s might, wholeheartedly - Full effort and concentration.
一生懸命頑張ります。 = いっしょうけんめい がんばります = isshōkenmei ganbarimasu = I will do my very best.
拷問 = ごうもん = gōmon = torture - Inflicting severe pain for punishment or information.
拷問に耐えられなかった。 = ごうもんに たえられなかった = gōmon ni taerarenakatta = He couldn’t endure the torture.
虐待 = ぎゃくたい = gyakutai = abuse, mistreatment - Ongoing physical or emotional abuse.
動物虐待は許されない。 = どうぶつぎゃくたいは ゆるされない = dōbutsu gyakutai wa yurusarenai = Animal abuse is unacceptable.
処刑 = しょけい = shokei = execution (capital punishment) - Legal killing as punishment.
死刑が執行され処刑された。 = しけいが しっこうされ しょけいされた = shikei ga shikkō sare shokei sareta = He was executed after the death sentence.
誇り = ほこり = hokori = pride, honor, dignity - Positive self-worth from achievements.
自分の仕事に誇りを持っている。 = じぶんの しごとに ほこりを もっている = jibun no shigoto ni hokori o motte iru = I take pride in my work.
5歳児に説明するように = ごさいじ に せつめい する ように = gosaiji ni setsumei suru yō ni = explain it like I’m a 5-year-old.
5歳児に説明するように教えて。 = ごさいじに せつめいするように おしえて = gosaiji ni setsumei suru yō ni oshiete = Explain it to me like I’m five years old.
盗んだ = ぬすんだ = nusunda = stole (past tense) - Took without permission.
財布を盗んだ犯人が捕まった。 = さいふを ぬすんだ はんにんが つかまった = saifu o nusunda hannin ga tsukamatta = The person who stole the wallet was caught.
奪った = うばった = ubatta = snatched, took by force - Violent or sudden seizure.
自由を奪った。 = じゆうを うばった = jiyū o ubatta = They took away our freedom.
略奪した = りゃくだつ した = ryōdatsu shita = plundered, looted - Large-scale organized theft.
村を略奪した。 = むらを りゃくだつした = mura o ryōdatsu shita = They plundered the village.
上半身 = じょうはんしん = jōhanshin = upper body - Part of the body above the waist.
上半身を鍛えている。 = じょうはんしんを きたえている = jōhanshin o kitaete iru = I am training my upper body.
暗黙 = あんもく = anmoku = implicit, tacit, unspoken, unsaid - Something understood or agreed upon without being directly expressed in words (unspoken rules or understandings).
彼は暗黙のうちに同意した。 = かれは あんもくの うちに どういした = kare wa anmoku no uchi ni dōi shita = He agreed implicitly / tacitly.
ただ…ってだけなのに = ただ…ってだけなのに = tada... tte dake nanoni = It's just... but still; Even though it's just...; Only... but yet - Expresses frustration or surprise that something big happens despite a simple/minor thing.
ただ挨拶しただけなのに、無視された。 = ただ あいさつしただけなのに、むしされた = tada aisatsu shita dake nanoni, mushi sareta = I only greeted him, but I got ignored.
ズバ抜けてる = ずばぬけてる = zubanuketeru = outstanding, exceptional, superb, head and shoulders above the rest - Remarkably better or more impressive than average; stands out sharply.
彼の才能はズバ抜けてる。 = かれの さいのうは ずばぬけてる = kare no sainō wa zubanuketeru = His talent is outstanding.
しかも = しかも = shikamo = moreover, furthermore, what's more, on top of that - Adds emphatic or surprising additional information that amplifies the previous statement.
値段が高い。しかも品質が悪い。 = ねだんが たかい。しかも ひんしつが わるい = nedan ga takai. shikamo hinshitsu ga warui = The price is high. What's more, the quality is bad.
キモい = きもい = kimoi = gross, disgusting, creepy, revolting - Strong informal slang for something that feels repulsive or creepy (stronger and more casual than 気持ち悪い).
その虫、キモい！ = そのむし、きもい！ = sono mushi, kimoi! = That bug is gross/creepy!
気持ち悪い = きもちわるい = kimochi warui = unpleasant, disgusting, gross, nauseating, creepy - More standard/polite way to express something feels bad or repulsive.
この絵、ちょっと気持ち悪い。 = このえ、ちょっと きもちわるい = kono e, chotto kimochi warui = This painting is a bit creepy/unpleasant.
ゾッとする = ぞっとする = zotto suru = to shudder, to feel a chill, to be horrified - Physical reaction of shuddering from something creepy, scary, or grotesque.
その話を聞いてゾッとした。 = そのはなしを きいて ぞっとした = sono hanashi o kiite zotto shita = Hearing that story gave me chills / made me shudder.
意味わかんない = いみわかんない = imi wakan nai = I don't get it, it makes no sense, I don't understand - Very casual way to express confusion or that something is illogical.
意味わかんないんだけど。 = いみわかんないんだけど = imi wakan nai n dakedo = I seriously don't get it.
いらってくる = いらってくる = ira tte kuru = to get irritated, to start feeling annoyed/frustrated - The feeling of irritation gradually building up.
だんだんいらってくる。 = だんだん いらってくる = dandan ira tte kuru = I'm starting to get irritated.
～に近い = ～にちかい = ~ ni chikai = close to ~, similar to ~, near to ~, bordering on ~ - Indicates proximity or similarity in quality/state.
彼の考えは私の考えに近い。 = かれの かんがえは わたしの かんがえに ちかい = kare no kangae wa watashi no kangae ni chikai = His thinking is close to mine.
謎 = なぞ = nazo = mystery, riddle, enigma, puzzle - Something unexplained, perplexing, or difficult to solve.
この事件はまだ謎が多い。 = このじけんはまだ なぞがおおい = kono jiken wa mada nazo ga ōi = There are still many mysteries surrounding this case.
結局 = けっきょく = kekkyoku = after all, in the end, ultimately, eventually - Indicates the final outcome or conclusion, often after much thought or time.
色々考えたけど、結局行かないことにした。 = いろいろ かんがえたけど、けっきょく いかないことにした = iroiro kangaeta kedo, kekkyoku ikanai koto ni shita = I thought about it a lot, but in the end I decided not to go.













